Bouteloua curtipendula

   [3796.jpg]
    Authority   (Michaux) Torrey
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 3796

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A grass reaching a height of 70-100 cm. USES Grown as
   a forage grass. KILLING T Winter-hardy. GROWING PERIOD Perennial. In
   the western United States it provides feed year round. COMMON NAMES
   Side-oats grama. FURTHER INF In the western United States it can be
   found in the dry woods and praities at elevations up to 2700 m. It also
   occurs in Central and South America south to northern Argentina and
   Bolivia. Side-oats grama is divided into two taxonomic groups, B.
   curtipendula var. curtipendula and var. caespitosa.

   Sources
   SOURCES (B. curtipendula (Michx.) Torr.)
   Bogdan A 1977 pp 53 [USE, DRA, LIG, DEP]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 178 [USE, DRA, LIG]
   Duke J 1975 pp 9 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Heath M 1985 pp 182 [USE, KTMP]

